      "span_text": "Natural climatic changes can increase host abundance and transmission of pathogens, as in the case of Sin Nombre hantavirus in the south-western USA. Increased rainfall resulted in more grass setting seed and expansion of rodent (Peromyscus spp.) populations which are natural reservoirs of the virus, and thereby greater human contact with these mice and their excretions [CITATION_1] ."
